2026-07-13 11:38:07,613 [DEBUG] groq._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/openai/v1/chat/completions', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-10b2230d-1277-43a3-971d-f9ddaad65a03', 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'system', 'content': 'You are a senior Product Manager writing an industry-standard Product Requirements Document (PRD).\n\nDo NOT include roadmaps, release timelines, sprint plans, Jira tasks, or user stories. Those are separate documents generated by dedicated agents.\n\nYou MUST respond ONLY with a raw JSON object. No markdown formatting, no backticks, no conversational text.\n\nThe JSON schema must be structured exactly as follows:\n{\n  "Executive_Summary": "A concise 2-3 sentence overview of the product and the problem it solves.",\n\n  "Product_Vision": "The long-term vision statement describing what the product aspires to become and why it matters.",\n\n  "Problem_Statement": "A precise description of the problem, for whom, and why existing solutions are insufficient.",\n\n  "Goals_and_Objectives": [\n    "Measurable objective 1 (e.g., Reduce patient wait time by 40% within 6 months)",\n    "Measurable objective 2"\n  ],\n\n  "Functional_Requirements": [\n    {\n      "id": "FR-001",\n      "title": "Short feature requirement title",\n      "description": "Detailed description of what the system must do.",\n      "priority": "High / Medium / Low",\n      "acceptance_criteria": "Specific testable condition that defines when this requirement is met."\n    }\n  ],\n\n  "Non_Functional_Requirements": {\n    "Performance": "Response time, throughput, and latency targets.",\n    "Scalability": "Expected load and horizontal/vertical scaling strategy.",\n    "Security": "Authentication, authorisation, encryption, and vulnerability standards.",\n    "Availability": "Uptime SLA and disaster recovery expectations.",\n    "Accessibility": "WCAG compliance level and assistive technology support.",\n    "Compliance": "Regulatory requirements (e.g., HIPAA, GDPR, SOC2) if applicable."\n  },\n\n  "Core_Features": [\n    {\n      "name": "Feature Name",\n      "description": "What this feature does and how it serves the user.",\n      "priority": "High / Medium / Low",\n      "business_value": "Why this feature matters to the business or user."\n    }\n  ],\n\n  "Assumptions": [\n    "Assumption 1 (e.g., Users have a stable internet connection)",\n    "Assumption 2"\n  ],\n\n  "Constraints": [\n    "Constraint 1 (e.g., Must integrate with legacy EHR system via HL7)",\n    "Constraint 2"\n  ],\n\n  "Success_Metrics": [\n    "KPI 1 (e.g., DAU growth of 15% month-over-month)",\n    "KPI 2"\n  ],\n\n  "Open_Questions": [\n    "Unresolved question 1 that needs a stakeholder decision",\n    "Unresolved question 2"\n  ]\n}\n\nPopulate every field based on the business analysis and product context provided. Be specific and thorough.'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': 'Retrieved Product Context:\nPrimary focus The “what” and “why” of the\nproduct\nThe “how” and “when” of\ndelivery\nMain\nresponsibility\nDefines product vision and\npriorities\nCoordinates execution\nand timelines\nCore goal Deliver long-term customer\nand business value\nKeep initiatives on track\nand completed\nsuccessfully\nTypical work\nPrioritizing features, shaping\nroadmap, understanding\ncustomer needs\nManaging tasks,\nschedules, resources, and\nmilestones\nMeasures\nsuccess by\nOutcomes, adoption, and\ncustomer impact\nDeliverables, deadlines,\nand execution quality\nWhile the titles sound similar, a product manager and a project manager handle very\ndifferent responsibilities. A product manager owns the "what" and "why" of a product. \nThey define the vision, prioritize features based on customer needs, and ensure the\n\nfrom great ones, and the frameworks that help teams ship products customers\nactually want to use.\nFree product roadmap template\nWhat is product management?\nProduct management guides a product’s lifecycle—from development to pricing—by\nprioritizing the product and its customers.\nTo build the best possible product, product managers advocate for customers within\nthe organization and make sure the voice of the market is heard and heeded. Thanks\nto this focus on the customer, product teams routinely ship better-designed and\nhigher-performing products.\nIn tech, where entrenched products are quickly uprooted by newer and better\nsolutions, there is more need than ever for an intimate understanding of customers.\nThere’s a need to create tailored solutions for them and that’s exactly where product\n\nProduct Interaction\nHow [Persona Name] Would Use Your Product\nDescribe how this persona would discover, evaluate, and use your product.\nUsage scenario...\nKey Features for This Persona\nWhich features matter most to them and why?\nFeature 1: [Feature name - why it matters to them]\nFeature 2: [Feature name - why it matters to them]\nFeature 3: [Feature name - why it matters to them]\nFeature 4: [Feature name - why it matters to them]\nFeature 5: [Feature name - why it matters to them]\nSuccess Metrics\nHow would this persona measure success with your product?\n• [Metric 1: e.g., Time saved per week]\n• [Metric 2: e.g., Increase in team productivity]\n• [Metric 3: e.g., Reduction in errors]\n• [Metric 4: e.g., Cost savings]\nObjections & Concerns\nWhat might prevent them from buying or using your product?\n\nBusiness Analysis JSON:\n{\n  "Problem Statement": "The current food delivery marketplaces are not optimized for eco-friendly shipping and zero-waste packaging, resulting in high carbon emissions and unnecessary waste. This problem statement is based on the user\'s product idea of a hyper-local food delivery marketplace that addresses these issues.",\n  "Business Goals": [\n    "Increase market share by 15% within the first year by targeting urban consumers aged 18-45 who prioritize eco-friendliness and sustainability.",\n    "Achieve a customer retention rate of 80% by providing a seamless and efficient delivery experience that reduces carbon emissions and waste.",\n    "Reduce carbon emissions by 20% within the first year by leveraging eco-friendly drone shipping and optimizing delivery routes.",\n    "Implement a zero-waste packaging system that reduces packaging waste by 30% within the first year."\n  ],\n  "User Personas": [\n    {\n      "name": "Eco-Conscious Emma",\n      "role": "Urban consumer aged 25-35 who prioritizes eco-friendliness and sustainability in their daily life.",\n      "needs": "A convenient and efficient food delivery experience that aligns with their values and reduces their carbon footprint. They need to be able to track the carbon emissions and waste generated by their food delivery orders and receive regular updates on the marketplace\'s sustainability efforts."\n    },\n    {\n      "name": "Busy Bee Sarah",\n      "role": "Urban consumer aged 18-25 who values convenience and speed in their food delivery experience.",\n      "needs": "A fast and reliable food delivery experience that meets their busy lifestyle. They need to be able to track their orders in real-time and receive updates on delivery status and estimated arrival times."\n    }\n  ]\n}\n'}], 'model': 'llama-3.1-8b-instant', 'n': 1, 'reasoning_effort': None, 'reasoning_format': None, 'service_tier': 'on_demand', 'stop': None, 'stream': False, 'temperature': 0.1}}
