hen [action], then [outcome].",\n        "Given [context], when [action], then [outcome]."\n      ],\n      "dependencies": [],\n      "traceability": {\n        "functional_requirements": ["FR-001"],\n        "business_goals": ["BG-001"]\n      },\n      "labels": ["frontend", "backend", "api", "auth", "notifications", "analytics"],\n      "risk": "Low | Medium | High",\n      "status": "To Do"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\nSTATUS VALUES — only use these exact strings:\n- For Epics: Draft, Ready, In Progress, Done\n- For Stories: To Do, In Progress, Blocked, Done\n\nPRIORITY VALUES — only use: Critical, High, Medium, Low\nCOMPLEXITY VALUES — only use: Low, Medium, High\nRELEASE VALUES — only use: MVP, Phase 1, Phase 2, Phase 3\n\nTRACEABILITY RULES:\n- functional_requirements: Reference IDs exactly as they appear in the PRD (e.g. FR-001, FR-002). MANDATORY for every story.\n- business_goals: Reference business goals from the Business Analysis when applicable. Use BG-001, BG-002, etc. to identify them by index if they have no IDs.\n\nSTORY FORMAT RULES:\n- Each Epic must contain between 3 and 8 stories.\n- Generate 2 to 4 Epics depending on the scope of the product.\n- The "persona" field must use real persona names from the Business Analysis (e.g. "Patient David", "Dr. Sarah"), not generic terms like "user" or "admin".\n- The "action" field should be the "I want to..." clause, written as a clear imperative.\n- The "value" field should be the "So that..." clause, written as a business or user outcome.\n- acceptance_criteria must use Given/When/Then format. Each story must have at least 2 criteria.\n- "dependencies" lists other story IDs (e.g. "US-002") this story depends on. Use an empty array if none.\n- "labels" are lowercase technical tags describing which system layer this story touches.\n- story_points must be Fibonacci: 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13.\n- "risk" reflects the delivery risk of implementing the story (Low, Medium, High).\n\nGenerate ONLY stories that are directly traceable to functional requirements in the supplied PRD. Quality over quantity.\n'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': '=== PROJECT CONTEXT ===\nProduct Idea: A hyper-local food delivery marketplace optimized for eco-friendly drone shipping and zero-waste packaging.\nIndustry: Food & Beverage\nProduct Type: Marketplace\nTarget Audience: Urban consumers aged 18-45\n\n=== BUSINESS ANALYSIS (source of personas and business goals) ===\n{\n  "Problem Statement": "The current food delivery marketplaces are not optimized for eco-friendly shipping and zero-waste packaging, resulting in high carbon emissions and unnecessary waste. This problem statement is based on the user\'s product idea of a hyper-local food delivery marketplace that addresses these issues.",\n  "Business Goals": [\n    "Increase market share by 15% within the first year by targeting urban consumers aged 18-45 who prioritize eco-friendliness and sustainability.",\n    "Achieve a customer retention rate of 80% by providing a seamless and efficient delivery experience that reduces carbon emissions and waste.",\n    "Reduce carbon emissions by 20% within the first year by leveraging eco-friendly drone shipping and optimizing delivery routes.",\n    "Implement a zero-waste packaging system that reduces packaging waste by 30% within the first year."\n  ],\n  "User Personas": [\n    {\n      "name": "Eco-Conscious Emma",\n      "role": "Urban consumer aged 25-35 who prioritizes eco-friendliness and sustainability in their daily life.",\n      "needs": "A convenient and efficient food delivery experience that aligns with their values and reduces their carbon footprint. They need to be able to track the carbon emissions and waste generated by their food delivery orders and receive regular updates on the marketplace\'s sustainability efforts."\n    },\n    {\n      "name": "Busy Bee Sarah",\n      "role": "Urban consumer aged 18-25 who values convenience and speed in their food delivery experience.",\n      "needs": "A fast and reliable food delivery experience that meets their busy lifestyle. They need to be able to track their orders in real-time and receive updates on delivery status and estimated arrival times."\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n=== PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT — PRIMARY SOURCE OF TRUTH ===\n{\n  "\\ud83d\\udccb Executive Summary": "Our product aims to revolutionize the food delivery market by introducing a hyper-local marketplace that prioritizes eco-friendly shipping and zero-waste packaging, reducing carbon emissions and unnecessary waste while providing a seamless and efficient delivery experience for urban consumers.",\n  "\\ud83d\\udd2d Product Vision": "To become the leading hyper-local food delivery marketplace that empowers consumers to make sustainable choices while delivering exceptional customer experiences and driving business growth through innovation and customer-centricity.",\n  "\\ud83c\\udfaf Problem Statement": "The current food delivery marketplaces are not optimized for eco-friendly shipping and zero-waste packaging, resulting in high carbon emissions and unnecessary waste. This problem statement is based on the user\'s product idea of a hyper-local food delivery marketplace that addresses these issues.",\n  "\\u2699\\ufe0f Functional Requirements": "**FR-001 \\u2014 User Profile Management** (Priority: High)\\nAllow users to create and manage their profiles, including setting eco-friendly preferences and tracking their carbon footprint.\\n*Acceptance Criteria:* Users can create and edit their profiles, and their eco-friendly preferences are reflected in the delivery experience.\\n\\n**FR-002 \\u2014 Eco-Friendly Shipping Options** (Priority: High)\\nProvide users with eco-friendly shipping options, including drone delivery and optimized delivery routes, to reduce carbon emissions.\\n*Acceptance Criteria:* Users can select eco-friendly shipping options, and the system calculates and displays the reduced carbon emissions.\\n\\n**FR-003 \\u2014 Zero-Waste Packaging System** (Priority: High)\\nImplement a zero-waste packaging system that reduces packaging waste by 30% within the first year.\\n*Acceptance Criteria:* The system generates zero-waste packaging for all orders, and packaging waste is tracked and reported.\\n\\n**FR-004 \\u2014 Real-Time Order Tracking** (Priority: Medium)\\nAllow users to track their orders in real-time, including estimated arrival times and delivery status.\\n*Acceptance Criteria:* Users can track their orders in real-time, and the system updates the delivery status and estimated arrival time."\n}\n\n=== INSTRUCTIONS ===\nGenerate Epics and User Stories that directly trace to the Functional Requirements above.\nReturn ONLY the raw JSON object. No markdown. No prose. No code fences.\nEvery story MUST include traceability.functional_requirements referencing exact FR IDs from the PRD.\n'}], 'model': 'llama-3.1-8b-instant', 'n': 1, 'reasoning_effort': None, 'reasoning_format': None, 'service_tier': 'on_demand', 'stop': None, 'stream': False, 'temperature': 0.1}}
